1
00:00:30,322 --> 00:00:33,951
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

2
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:46,879
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION
SOME SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

3
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:48,966
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

4
00:01:23,166 --> 00:01:24,418
I just got my hooks in.

5
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:30,799
Where do we go from here?

6
00:02:53,256 --> 00:02:54,799
You can sit comfortably.

7
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,510
Why are you kneeling?

8
00:02:59,471 --> 00:03:01,890
Cut it out, Grandma. You're scaring us.

9
00:03:03,475 --> 00:03:05,894
What were you two doing outside
so late at night?

10
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:11,066
Don't you know there are always people
watching on this tiny island?

11
00:03:12,234 --> 00:03:14,610
Today is officially day one for us.

12
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:16,362
What did you just say?

13
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:19,281
I like Ms. Hari a lot, ma'am.

14
00:03:19,282 --> 00:03:20,450
Well, I don't like you!

15
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:23,537
What? Why don't you like him?

16
00:03:24,121 --> 00:03:26,915
He's so frail
you had to carry him on your back,

17
00:03:27,791 --> 00:03:31,128
but most importantly,
he put you in danger.

18
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:39,009
If Hari were to go out with someone,

19
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:42,889
I'd like him
to be someone she can rely on.

20
00:03:44,141 --> 00:03:45,224
Grandma, he's also--

21
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:48,228
Yes, so I'll try harder…

22
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:51,939
to earn your trust, ma'am.

23
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:54,775
That won't ever happen,
so don't even bother trying.

24
00:03:54,776 --> 00:03:56,862
It's getting late, so be on your way now.

25
00:04:07,164 --> 00:04:09,415
I told you, it's no use!

26
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,709
Get up.

27
00:04:13,462 --> 00:04:14,754
That's not exactly…

28
00:04:19,176 --> 00:04:20,342
My legs cramped up.

29
00:04:20,343 --> 00:04:21,344
I'm so sorry.

30
00:04:23,597 --> 00:04:24,931
Unbelievable.

31
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:35,400
- Are you okay?
- Mm-hmm.

32
00:04:36,485 --> 00:04:39,863
It's just because
she worries about me a lot.

33
00:04:41,364 --> 00:04:44,034
Well, she has every reason to be worried.

34
00:04:45,577 --> 00:04:47,370
But I'm going to show her

35
00:04:47,871 --> 00:04:50,956
that I'm perfectly capable
of keeping you safe.

36
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:53,459
What?

37
00:04:53,460 --> 00:04:55,211
It's a snake.

38
00:04:55,212 --> 00:04:58,005
- A snake in your front yard?
- A snake?

39
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:01,301
- Huh? Why would you grab it? Oh, man…
- Okay, I got it!

40
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,053
I got it!

41
00:05:04,054 --> 00:05:05,846
- Don't do it.
- What's wrong?

42
00:05:05,847 --> 00:05:07,723
- It's kind of cute. Look!
- Put it down.

43
00:05:07,724 --> 00:05:10,851
- What's wrong?
- Come on. Stop it!

44
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:12,895
Come on. It's so cute from up close.

45
00:05:12,896 --> 00:05:14,605
Just let it go!

46
00:05:14,606 --> 00:05:17,399
I'll let it go. I'm letting it go now!

47
00:05:19,361 --> 00:05:23,197
Huh? You'll run into a lot of snakes
if you go that way.

48
00:05:25,575 --> 00:05:30,705
EPISODE 6
AN UNSPEAKABLE SECRET

49
00:05:34,793 --> 00:05:36,711
I saw
the slippers you threw out.

50
00:05:37,796 --> 00:05:41,299
You did that because you didn't want to
wear the same ones as me, right?

51
00:05:43,927 --> 00:05:46,428
I'll stop wearing mine,
so you can wear those.

52
00:05:46,429 --> 00:05:48,097
You hurt your foot.

53
00:05:48,098 --> 00:05:50,559
Those are the lightest,
most comfortable shoes around.

54
00:05:51,810 --> 00:05:54,604
So you bought another pair
of these expensive slippers?

55
00:05:55,897 --> 00:05:56,898
Um, yes.

56
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:58,483
Ah…

57
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:01,861
I threw them out
because they were knockoffs.

58
00:06:01,862 --> 00:06:04,488
I was embarrassed and annoyed about that.

59
00:06:04,489 --> 00:06:08,242
Not that Your Highness would have known
that knockoffs even existed.

60
00:06:08,243 --> 00:06:10,744
So take these back and get a refund.

61
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:11,954
I'll pass.

62
00:06:11,955 --> 00:06:17,668
-  Can't you just wear them?
- What?

63
00:06:17,669 --> 00:06:20,671
I know your foot is hurting
like crazy right now,

64
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:23,550
and these are
the comfiest shoes I've ever worn.

65
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:26,970
But still, this is too much.

66
00:06:28,013 --> 00:06:29,305
Good morning.

67
00:06:29,306 --> 00:06:31,516
-  Hello.
-  Hello.

68
00:06:35,478 --> 00:06:36,854
Are you fighting again?

69
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:38,439
Not at all.

70
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:41,066
I told you to get along,
but you fight like children.

71
00:06:41,067 --> 00:06:42,276
It's not even noon yet!

72
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:44,486
It's not what you think.

73
00:06:48,783 --> 00:06:51,118
I just really wanted
to get you a pair,

74
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:53,663
so do whatever you want with them.

75
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:57,292
See you.

76
00:07:03,965 --> 00:07:07,176
-  Did you sleep well?
- Oh, yes.

77
00:07:07,177 --> 00:07:10,013
- How about you, Dr. Do?
- Me too.

78
00:07:12,682 --> 00:07:15,143
-  Let me give that a go.
- Huh? Oh…

79
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:21,941
Damn.

80
00:07:27,489 --> 00:07:28,822
Here.

81
00:07:28,823 --> 00:07:29,908
It's fine.

82
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:35,455
You can't even get that open?

83
00:07:38,458 --> 00:07:39,626
Oh.

84
00:07:43,713 --> 00:07:46,256
Ms. Hari, can we talk for a moment?

85
00:07:46,257 --> 00:07:47,633
Sure.

86
00:07:47,634 --> 00:07:49,469
- Excuse me for a moment.
- Sure.

87
00:07:52,389 --> 00:07:54,474
Ah… Almost walked off with these.

88
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:06,276
-  Oh, my. Welcome.
- Hi.

89
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:10,322
-  Wait here for just a moment.
- I did most of the work getting it open.

90
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:12,491
Dr. Jiui, a patient's here to see you.

91
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:14,119
- A patient?
-  Hurry.

92
00:08:17,789 --> 00:08:19,456
Hello. How's your tongue?

93
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:21,710
It's completely healed now.

94
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:23,795
Please take a seat here.

95
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:28,215
What brings you here?

96
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:31,009
I checked my blood sugar levels
at the senior center,

97
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,680
- and damn it, I got a reading of 280.
- 280?

98
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:37,683
Did you have anything else
besides makgeolli?

99
00:08:37,684 --> 00:08:40,477
Yes, well…

100
00:08:40,478 --> 00:08:44,231
I mean, it's the darndest thing,
but I didn't have anything to eat.

101
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:45,316
What the hell?

102
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:50,696
Okay, this one time,
I just had a sip of makgeolli,

103
00:08:50,697 --> 00:08:52,574
- and that was it.
- Are you kidding me?

104
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:56,118
Are you telling me
I can't even drink that much?

105
00:08:56,119 --> 00:08:57,870
I can't even.

106
00:08:57,871 --> 00:09:02,249
Okay. I'll stop drinking makgeolli, okay?

107
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:05,127
I'll also start working out,
so don't worry.

108
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:09,965
I'll take good care of myself
and come again next week.

109
00:09:09,966 --> 00:09:11,051
Sure.

110
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,886
Take care.

111
00:09:15,597 --> 00:09:20,059
Dr. Do Jiui sure cares
a lot about his patients.

112
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:21,935
He cares more than my wife!

113
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:23,687
Let me help you with your payment.

114
00:09:23,688 --> 00:09:26,982
I'm just going to leave today
and come back next week.

115
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:28,734
Okay, have a safe trip back.

116
00:09:28,735 --> 00:09:30,319
INBOX

117
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,864
SEND MESSAGE

118
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:36,034
Not curious or anything.

119
00:09:36,618 --> 00:09:38,786
Just wondering
if it's something I should know.

120
00:09:38,787 --> 00:09:41,205
What did you talk about?
Was it about the center?

121
00:09:41,206 --> 00:09:42,540
YUK HARI

122
00:09:45,335 --> 00:09:47,420
Would I seem too petty if I sent this?

123
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,637
Is something wrong with Dr. Chiyeon?

124
00:09:56,638 --> 00:09:58,680
Why did he pull you aside
during work hours?

125
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:00,141
YUK HARI

126
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:05,813
Dr. Do, my grandma's been approved
for the clinical trial.

127
00:10:05,814 --> 00:10:06,981
She'll have tests tomorrow.

128
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:15,280
Wow, I'm so happy for you.

129
00:10:15,281 --> 00:10:16,866
Congratulations, Ms. Yuk.

130
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:21,871
Ah…

131
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,585
Look at him, trying to play it cool.

132
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:36,511
He's so adorable.

133
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:45,061
Hello, you've reached
the Public Health Center.

134
00:10:48,064 --> 00:10:49,398
Tomorrow?

135
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:53,403
The governor said he wants to meet me?

136
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:56,655
You saved Deokhwa's life.

137
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:59,283
It sounded like he wanted
to commend you for that.

138
00:10:59,284 --> 00:11:02,536
He said you're the perfect symbol
of Yeopoong's healthcare modernization.

139
00:11:02,537 --> 00:11:04,288
But it's not like I did it by myself.

140
00:11:04,289 --> 00:11:07,624
Exactly,
so when you meet the governor,

141
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:10,043
put in a good word for us, okay?

142
00:11:10,044 --> 00:11:11,503
And get him to replace…

143
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:15,757
Why isn't she wearing them?
Those shoes must be uncomfortable.

144
00:11:15,758 --> 00:11:19,136
But wouldn't we be short-staffed tomorrow?

145
00:11:19,137 --> 00:11:21,930
We're supposed to visit the Senior Center
to treat the grandmas.

146
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:24,641
Since when did the higher-ups care
about any of that?

147
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:27,019
We'll have to manage on our own somehow.

148
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,395
Mmm…

149
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:29,689
Why won't she wear them?

150
00:11:30,899 --> 00:11:33,358
Gosh, you've been
mumbling to yourself nonstop.

151
00:11:33,359 --> 00:11:34,735
What are you mumbling about?

152
00:11:36,279 --> 00:11:37,280
Huh?

153
00:11:39,282 --> 00:11:42,576
It's nothing. Thank you for the meal.

154
00:11:42,577 --> 00:11:45,205
You've barely touched your food again!

155
00:11:47,624 --> 00:11:50,500
You're gonna go
and eat gummy worms again, aren't you?

156
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:51,585
I'm not!

157
00:11:51,586 --> 00:11:54,421
- I'd better not catch you eating them.
- You don't even know.

158
00:11:54,422 --> 00:11:56,340
That's why he can't put on any weight.

159
00:11:56,341 --> 00:11:58,218
So frustrating.

160
00:12:03,389 --> 00:12:07,351
I wish I could go with you,
but I'm swamped with work at the center.

161
00:12:07,352 --> 00:12:10,604
But they said the tests today
won't be too demanding.

162
00:12:10,605 --> 00:12:13,065
- But…
- Yes?

163
00:12:13,066 --> 00:12:16,443
…what's this about a clinical trial
all of a sudden?

164
00:12:16,444 --> 00:12:18,570
- Hari, I--
- Grandma.

165
00:12:18,571 --> 00:12:21,574
I heard a super famous professor's
in charge of these trials.

166
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:25,702
On top of that, I heard some patients
who were worse off than you

167
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:27,162
already saw some improvements.

168
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:28,580
Okay.

169
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:30,874
But Hari, the thing is--

170
00:12:30,875 --> 00:12:34,545
Let's go on a trip together
once your treatment is over.

171
00:12:35,546 --> 00:12:38,882
There's so much
we didn't get to do together

172
00:12:38,883 --> 00:12:41,469
because I was busy studying
and you were busy making money.

173
00:12:43,721 --> 00:12:47,516
- Right. Let's do that.
- Mmm.

174
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:51,270
- The ferry for Yeopoong is now departing.
- Goodness, hurry up and go now.

175
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:52,437
Don't worry about me.

176
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:53,772
Get going now.

177
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:55,691
- Have a safe trip, okay?
- Okay.

178
00:12:55,692 --> 00:12:58,819
Hurry up and get going.

179
00:13:04,158 --> 00:13:05,535
Huh?

180
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:09,914
I wonder if Dr. Do managed
to board without any issues.

181
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:47,660
Are you okay?

182
00:13:49,454 --> 00:13:50,538
Sorry?

183
00:13:54,042 --> 00:13:56,878
I just couldn't bring myself
to ignore you.

184
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:03,843
Oh, dear, you look really seasick.

185
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:06,637
Oh, yes.

186
00:14:50,807 --> 00:14:52,558
What's with that shirt?

187
00:14:53,142 --> 00:14:55,311
You look so sloppy. At least sew it up.

188
00:14:57,438 --> 00:14:58,856
Hmm?

189
00:15:01,359 --> 00:15:03,777
- It's okay.
- It's not okay.

190
00:15:03,778 --> 00:15:06,030
You look like a total slob.

191
00:15:08,699 --> 00:15:11,327
I'm only going to wear it here
and throw it out.

192
00:15:12,078 --> 00:15:14,664
Only going to wear it here,
then throw it out?

193
00:15:22,463 --> 00:15:24,632
A comfy pair of slippers
would be good for you.

194
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:31,013
These are comfy enough.

195
00:15:35,101 --> 00:15:38,938
The ferry bound for
Cheongmokdo is now departing.

196
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:42,024
Oh, my. Hey.

197
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:43,568
Huh?

198
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:45,903
Are you okay?

199
00:15:46,571 --> 00:15:48,990
You look pale as a ghost.

200
00:15:50,658 --> 00:15:53,160
Yes, I'm okay.

201
00:15:53,161 --> 00:15:54,162
Hmm…

202
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:57,331
Well then, be on your way.

203
00:15:58,124 --> 00:15:59,375
Would you…

204
00:16:01,502 --> 00:16:06,423
Would you like for me
to accompany you to the hospital?

205
00:16:08,926 --> 00:16:10,636
W-What for?

206
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:14,097
Since you were next to me
when I was scared,

207
00:16:14,098 --> 00:16:16,976
I figured I'd return the favor.

208
00:16:17,685 --> 00:16:19,561
What's there to be scared of?

209
00:16:19,562 --> 00:16:21,606
Do you take me for a child?

210
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:30,489
MUJI HOSPITAL

211
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:44,127
-  Yes, Ms. Yuk.
-  Did you arrive in one piece?

212
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:46,713
I'm at the hospital
with your grandmother right now.

213
00:16:46,714 --> 00:16:49,425
- I need to be there by the afternoon, so--
- My grandma?

214
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:51,343
How's she doing?

215
00:16:51,344 --> 00:16:52,345
Is she all right?

216
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:54,930
I'll get back to you
once the tests are done.

217
00:16:54,931 --> 00:16:56,473
Okay. Give me a call.

218
00:16:56,474 --> 00:16:57,475
Okay.

219
00:17:20,331 --> 00:17:21,332
Are you nervous?

220
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,710
What's there to be nervous about?

221
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:32,635
They'll be testing you to see
how you respond to the treatment

222
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:36,638
before you undergo the clinical trials.

223
00:17:36,639 --> 00:17:39,559
It's a simple test,
so there's nothing to be afraid of.

224
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:46,816
So I might really undergo clinical trials
once they finish testing me today?

225
00:17:48,609 --> 00:17:50,194
What would that be like?

226
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:54,322
Well, I think…

227
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:57,325
Forget it.
Don't even bother answering.

228
00:17:57,326 --> 00:17:59,995
I know you'll tell me
that everything will be fine.

229
00:17:59,996 --> 00:18:02,081
That everything will be fine.

230
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:07,336
I'm sure the hospital staff
will give you a rundown.

231
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:12,216
But the clinical trial process
won't be a walk in the park.

232
00:18:14,260 --> 00:18:16,137
If you were to suffer any side effects…

233
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:18,931
it might put you in even greater danger.

234
00:18:22,893 --> 00:18:25,146
Cancer's never easy on the patient.

235
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:28,149
- Mmm…
- That's why…

236
00:18:30,026 --> 00:18:32,153
if it's too hard, you can say so.

237
00:18:34,405 --> 00:18:35,406
Okay.

238
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:09,398
All done.

239
00:19:10,232 --> 00:19:13,653
Apply some pressure on it,
and once the bleeding stops, put this on.

240
00:19:32,505 --> 00:19:36,341
We're going to do an ECG now,
so please stay seated here for a moment.

241
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:37,510
- Okay.
- Right.

242
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:21,554
Ms. Oh Mija,
let me take you to get that ECG now.

243
00:20:22,138 --> 00:20:23,472
Ms. Oh Mija!

244
00:20:24,598 --> 00:20:26,267
Ms. Oh Mija, are you here?

245
00:20:27,393 --> 00:20:28,394
Excuse me.

246
00:20:29,603 --> 00:20:31,980
Didn't Ms. Oh Mija go inside
to get examined?

247
00:20:31,981 --> 00:20:35,401
I told her to sit here and wait,
but I don't see her.

248
00:20:37,403 --> 00:20:41,282
- Uh… P-Please wait for just a moment.
- Oh…

249
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:55,629
The number you've dialed
cannot be reached at this time.

250
00:21:07,808 --> 00:21:09,350
Is my grandma doing all right?

251
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:11,519
DR. DODO

252
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:13,189
Do give me a call when it's over.

253
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:27,452
WHAT IS AN ADVANCE DIRECTIVE?

254
00:21:27,453 --> 00:21:29,287
A LEGAL DOCUMENT
STATING AN ADULT'S WISHES

255
00:21:29,288 --> 00:21:30,456
REGARDING END-OF-LIFE CARE

256
00:21:40,633 --> 00:21:42,218
What are you doing here?

257
00:21:43,719 --> 00:21:47,555
Goodness, what is the matter with you?

258
00:21:47,556 --> 00:21:50,558
I told you I'd take care of it myself,

259
00:21:50,559 --> 00:21:52,685
so please just leave me alone.

260
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:53,938
Oh, my.

261
00:22:11,956 --> 00:22:12,957
Ma'am.

262
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:19,296
If you're scared,
it's okay to tell me that you're scared.

263
00:22:20,214 --> 00:22:21,714
I told you I'm not scared.

264
00:22:21,715 --> 00:22:25,010
I also tried to hide the fact
that I was scared of the sea,

265
00:22:25,511 --> 00:22:27,054
but Ms. Hari found out.

266
00:22:30,474 --> 00:22:31,934
But I actually felt relieved…

267
00:22:34,228 --> 00:22:35,646
once it was out in the open.

268
00:22:36,981 --> 00:22:38,774
I could be as scared as I wanted.

269
00:22:41,652 --> 00:22:44,071
So it's okay to be afraid.

270
00:23:25,613 --> 00:23:30,576
I had no intention of going through
with the clinical trials to begin with.

271
00:23:32,453 --> 00:23:38,709
I also know
that I don't have much time left.

272
00:23:41,253 --> 00:23:43,422
Five years after I received chemotherapy,

273
00:23:44,465 --> 00:23:46,842
they declared that I was cancer-free.

274
00:23:48,594 --> 00:23:54,475
Hari and I hugged each other
and cried so much, saying it was all over…

275
00:23:56,894 --> 00:23:57,895
But goodness…

276
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:02,775
Turns out cancer is incredibly stubborn.

277
00:24:03,359 --> 00:24:06,236
It won't ever relent
until it's taken everything from you.

278
00:24:08,822 --> 00:24:11,658
Going back and forth to the hospital

279
00:24:11,659 --> 00:24:14,370
to receive
the painful treatment was scary,

280
00:24:15,663 --> 00:24:18,457
and the thought of death
was also terrifying.

281
00:24:20,626 --> 00:24:23,128
But what scared me the most…

282
00:25:02,793 --> 00:25:07,089
…was spending my final moments
looking like an empty shell,

283
00:25:07,589 --> 00:25:10,217
neither alive nor dead.

284
00:25:18,600 --> 00:25:22,438
I just want to keep going about my day
as I always have

285
00:25:23,439 --> 00:25:26,108
and eventually die as Hari's grandmother.

286
00:25:27,484 --> 00:25:29,403
That is my wish.

287
00:25:35,200 --> 00:25:37,493
That's awfully selfish of me, isn't it?

288
00:25:37,494 --> 00:25:39,621
You must think I'm a terrible grandmother.

289
00:25:41,081 --> 00:25:44,668
If Hari were to find out,
she'd be devastated.

290
00:25:46,503 --> 00:25:48,672
That's what you're thinking, isn't it?

291
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:51,341
Not at all.

292
00:25:54,845 --> 00:25:56,096
You…

293
00:25:58,182 --> 00:25:59,641
must have been so lonely.

294
00:26:01,852 --> 00:26:03,312
That's what I'm thinking.

295
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:09,693
You must've been terrified,
dealing with this alone.

296
00:26:25,542 --> 00:26:26,794
Yes, Ms. Yuk.

297
00:26:29,129 --> 00:26:30,672
They're still examining her.

298
00:26:31,757 --> 00:26:33,759
I'll get back to you once it's over.

299
00:26:36,553 --> 00:26:37,554
Okay.

300
00:26:47,815 --> 00:26:52,694
I LOVE YEOPOONG

301
00:27:04,706 --> 00:27:05,791
Hello.

302
00:27:07,042 --> 00:27:09,836
- You're Dr. Do Jiui, right?
- Yes.

303
00:27:09,837 --> 00:27:11,088
I see. Right this way.

304
00:27:18,762 --> 00:27:21,014
Oh. Hello. This way.

305
00:27:25,435 --> 00:27:27,562
Oh, my.

306
00:27:27,563 --> 00:27:31,107
Dr. Do Jiui.

307
00:27:31,108 --> 00:27:34,902
When they heard that I'd be meeting you,

308
00:27:34,903 --> 00:27:37,280
the reporters were dying of curiosity…

309
00:27:37,281 --> 00:27:40,324
- Over here. Please look this way.
- …and came all this way.

310
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:43,828
Just act natural and try to relax.

311
00:27:43,829 --> 00:27:46,080
- It's not natural at all.
- Relax.

312
00:27:46,081 --> 00:27:47,582
Please look this way too.

313
00:27:47,583 --> 00:27:48,666
KO CHANGMOK WILL LEAD

314
00:27:48,667 --> 00:27:50,585
YEOPOONG-GUN'S
HEALTHCARE MODERNIZATION

315
00:27:50,586 --> 00:27:55,549
The child was having trouble breathing
due to acute epiglottitis.

316
00:27:58,427 --> 00:28:03,347
We had to get her to a hospital quickly,
so we took the village chief's boat,

317
00:28:03,348 --> 00:28:06,142
and all the medical staff on the scene

318
00:28:06,143 --> 00:28:08,353
did all they could
to save the child's life.

319
00:28:13,942 --> 00:28:16,445
Did you receive any help
from the county office?

320
00:28:17,154 --> 00:28:18,446
The county office--

321
00:28:18,447 --> 00:28:22,034
Just tell them what happened.
No need to hold back.

322
00:28:23,452 --> 00:28:26,955
Well, the…

323
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:34,670
I see our good doctor's really nervous.

324
00:28:34,671 --> 00:28:38,842
I, Ko Changmok,
will do everything in my power

325
00:28:39,509 --> 00:28:42,470
to fully support these islands

326
00:28:42,471 --> 00:28:48,435
so that they can bring any patient
back to life right away. Okay?

327
00:28:48,977 --> 00:28:54,690
That's why we're renovating
20 helipads…

328
00:28:54,691 --> 00:28:57,360
…in remote locations
throughout the county.

329
00:29:15,087 --> 00:29:20,883
Goodness, you've done wonders for
Yeopoong-gun's public image, Dr. Do Jiui.

330
00:29:21,969 --> 00:29:26,514
Now then, a toast to Dr. Do Jiui!

331
00:29:26,515 --> 00:29:28,349
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

332
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:30,727
Thank you, Dr. Do.

333
00:29:33,355 --> 00:29:34,438
MS. YUK HARI

334
00:29:34,439 --> 00:29:36,732
- We're counting on you.
- Let me pour you one.

335
00:29:36,733 --> 00:29:38,609
- Oh, my.
- Let me pour you one.

336
00:29:38,610 --> 00:29:40,361
The number you've called

337
00:29:40,362 --> 00:29:42,864
- cannot be reached at this time.
- I guess he's busy.

338
00:29:43,991 --> 00:29:45,492
I miss him.

339
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:52,040
Make sure you call me even if it's late.

340
00:29:52,541 --> 00:29:54,292
I miss you.

341
00:30:29,244 --> 00:30:30,494
Hello?

342
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:32,496
I'm sorry. Did I wake you up?

343
00:30:32,497 --> 00:30:34,416
No, you didn't.

344
00:30:36,043 --> 00:30:37,918
Why are you up so soon, though?

345
00:30:37,919 --> 00:30:39,212
What time is your ferry?

346
00:30:40,088 --> 00:30:41,965
The earliest one.

347
00:30:43,592 --> 00:30:44,634
The earliest one?

348
00:30:46,845 --> 00:30:48,930
Oh… It must have left already, though.

349
00:30:49,473 --> 00:30:52,225
Can you come outside
your house for a moment?

350
00:30:52,726 --> 00:30:53,727
I miss you.

351
00:30:55,604 --> 00:30:56,772
Outside my house?

352
00:30:58,523 --> 00:31:00,567
Dr. Do!

353
00:31:02,611 --> 00:31:04,446
What the heck?

354
00:31:05,030 --> 00:31:07,490
I'm sorry I couldn't pick up last night.

355
00:31:07,491 --> 00:31:10,701
I came as soon as I could.
I waited at the port for the first ferry.

356
00:31:10,702 --> 00:31:12,286
You didn't have to do that.

357
00:31:12,287 --> 00:31:14,789
- You must be exhausted.
- I missed you.

358
00:31:17,084 --> 00:31:20,837
And how did you get along with my grandma?
Did you manage okay on the ferry?

359
00:31:22,756 --> 00:31:24,132
Yes, I suppose.

360
00:31:26,134 --> 00:31:27,384
Don't you worry.

361
00:31:27,385 --> 00:31:30,721
My grandma always lets me have my way,
so if I keep telling her I like you,

362
00:31:30,722 --> 00:31:32,681
I'm sure she'll change her mind.

363
00:31:36,561 --> 00:31:37,562
Ms. Yuk.

364
00:31:48,031 --> 00:31:52,536
I'll be by your side,
no matter what happens. Okay?

365
00:31:56,331 --> 00:31:57,749
I'll do the same.

366
00:32:27,362 --> 00:32:28,946
GOVERNOR OF YEOPOONG-GUN

367
00:32:28,947 --> 00:32:31,867
REASSIGNMENT ORDER
FOR PUBLIC HEALTH DOCTOR DO JIUI

368
00:32:32,534 --> 00:32:36,162
"Saving her life
wouldn't have been possible

369
00:32:36,163 --> 00:32:38,706
without Governor Ko Changmok's help"?

370
00:32:42,961 --> 00:32:47,798
"PH doc Do Jiui extends his gratitude
to Governor Ko Changmok,

371
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:50,385
who supported their cause
in every way possible--"

372
00:32:51,761 --> 00:32:54,054
I didn't take you for that kind of guy.

373
00:32:54,055 --> 00:32:55,723
You cozy up to powerful people, huh?

374
00:32:55,724 --> 00:32:57,850
- No, wait…
-  Judging by that photo,

375
00:32:57,851 --> 00:33:00,811
people might think
the two of you were best buds.

376
00:33:00,812 --> 00:33:03,272
I didn't take you
for a man of such ambition.

377
00:33:03,273 --> 00:33:04,565
They twisted my words.

378
00:33:04,566 --> 00:33:06,567
I talked about our center a lot, okay?

379
00:33:06,568 --> 00:33:09,403
- I can't even…
- Yes. I'm sure you did.

380
00:33:09,404 --> 00:33:11,322
That Ko Changmok, damn it.

381
00:33:11,323 --> 00:33:13,073
Is there a doctor here?

382
00:33:13,074 --> 00:33:16,619
A doctor! Come out here!

383
00:33:16,620 --> 00:33:18,121
Goodness, what's this about?

384
00:33:52,948 --> 00:33:54,950
- This is going to sting.
- Okay.

385
00:33:57,661 --> 00:34:01,706
Hang in there.
Keep those eyes shut.

386
00:34:02,457 --> 00:34:03,458
Holy hell.

387
00:34:04,668 --> 00:34:06,585
How on earth did this happen?

388
00:34:06,586 --> 00:34:08,505
He fell over at a construction site.

389
00:34:09,339 --> 00:34:11,340
They've been rushing this project,

390
00:34:11,341 --> 00:34:13,385
so someone was bound to get injured.

391
00:34:16,263 --> 00:34:19,683
What's this
I hear about an accident?

392
00:34:20,308 --> 00:34:22,559
What happened?

393
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:24,271
What kind of accident?

394
00:34:26,022 --> 00:34:30,234
Jeez, how useless could you be?

395
00:34:30,235 --> 00:34:34,113
You took the money, mucked up your job

396
00:34:34,114 --> 00:34:35,991
and now here you are, slacking off.

397
00:34:36,700 --> 00:34:38,033
I'm sorry, sir.

398
00:34:38,034 --> 00:34:40,828
How the hell could you say that?
A man is injured.

399
00:34:40,829 --> 00:34:43,914
That's why you lot should have stuck
to the safety protocols!

400
00:34:43,915 --> 00:34:47,876
How are you going to make up
for all the time lost because of this?

401
00:34:47,877 --> 00:34:49,795
- How?
- A man's been injured!

402
00:34:49,796 --> 00:34:52,007
Who cares about time lost? Huh?

403
00:34:52,716 --> 00:34:57,636
I care about the time lost, you oaf.

404
00:34:57,637 --> 00:34:58,888
Time is money.

405
00:34:59,514 --> 00:35:02,683
You'd better not use this as an excuse
to spout some crap like,

406
00:35:02,684 --> 00:35:05,311
"We're out of funds,"
or "We need more time."

407
00:35:05,312 --> 00:35:07,188
I'll kill you all if you do.

408
00:35:15,447 --> 00:35:18,032
Jeez, we're already
running behind schedule.

409
00:35:18,033 --> 00:35:20,409
- What a nightmare.
- I'm gonna kill this asshole.

410
00:35:20,410 --> 00:35:22,578
Hey! You heartless bastard.

411
00:35:22,579 --> 00:35:25,706
Don't you even care that a man's injured?
Huh?

412
00:35:25,707 --> 00:35:28,000
Let go of me.
Have you completely lost it?

413
00:35:28,001 --> 00:35:31,295
Yeah, I've completely lost it!
What choice do I have but to go crazy?

414
00:35:31,296 --> 00:35:32,963
I told you, didn't I?

415
00:35:32,964 --> 00:35:35,049
That we'd end up dying
if you kept rushing us.

416
00:35:35,050 --> 00:35:38,052
- What are you all doing? Stop him!
- No one try to stop me!

417
00:35:38,053 --> 00:35:39,762
-  Please…
- I'm going to kill you,

418
00:35:39,763 --> 00:35:41,555
- then kill myself today.
- Okay!

419
00:35:41,556 --> 00:35:44,434
All right, man. Then how about this?
I give you more time…

420
00:35:46,478 --> 00:35:48,271
I'll kill you!

421
00:35:49,022 --> 00:35:50,523
What the…

422
00:35:56,237 --> 00:35:59,114
That's enough. There are patients here.

423
00:35:59,115 --> 00:36:02,242
I'm the one who was attacked!

424
00:36:02,243 --> 00:36:04,496
I'm the victim here!

425
00:36:05,580 --> 00:36:09,500
It seems the accident has caused
a lot of ill will between you.

426
00:36:09,501 --> 00:36:11,836
Why don't you make up here?

427
00:36:13,797 --> 00:36:17,550
Listen. I should be suing you for this.

428
00:36:18,301 --> 00:36:20,844
But I'll let it slide
since we're pressed for time.

429
00:36:20,845 --> 00:36:22,888
What are you still doing here? Scram.

430
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:24,056
- Why, you…
- Hey…

431
00:36:24,057 --> 00:36:25,058
Stop. That's enough.

432
00:36:26,851 --> 00:36:27,936
You should get going.

433
00:36:28,478 --> 00:36:31,064
Right. Thank you so much, Doctor.

434
00:36:31,981 --> 00:36:33,191
- Jeez.
- Come on.

435
00:36:33,775 --> 00:36:35,026
Let's go.

436
00:36:42,492 --> 00:36:44,202
I can't let you leave just yet, sir.

437
00:36:45,870 --> 00:36:47,371
What now?

438
00:36:47,372 --> 00:36:49,082
I told you last time, didn't I?

439
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:52,626
Interfering with medical care
is an aggravated crime.

440
00:36:52,627 --> 00:36:53,919
Damn it.

441
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:56,797
Why are you telling me that?

442
00:36:56,798 --> 00:36:59,884
I'm the one who was attacked!

443
00:37:01,428 --> 00:37:03,096
If this ever happens again…

444
00:37:05,056 --> 00:37:06,890
I won't let it slide.

445
00:37:06,891 --> 00:37:09,519
Wow, this is unbelievable.

446
00:37:10,061 --> 00:37:13,230
So what if you won't let it slide?
What will you do about it?

447
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:14,481
What will you do?

448
00:37:14,482 --> 00:37:16,734
Hey, hey, hey.

449
00:37:16,735 --> 00:37:19,945
- Dr. Hyeon.
- Let go.

450
00:37:19,946 --> 00:37:24,700
Our doctor tends to spout nonsense
when he gets agitated.

451
00:37:24,701 --> 00:37:25,784
He's just like that.

452
00:37:25,785 --> 00:37:27,328
Nonsense…

453
00:37:28,705 --> 00:37:31,457
They're just kids.
I'll give them a good scolding.

454
00:37:31,458 --> 00:37:33,418
You don't want to get into a fight.

455
00:37:34,043 --> 00:37:36,920
That's the second time
she's saved your life.

456
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:39,882
Strike three,
and you're really going to get it!

457
00:37:39,883 --> 00:37:42,426
You're the bigger man.

458
00:37:42,427 --> 00:37:44,636
They're just immature kids.

459
00:37:44,637 --> 00:37:47,181
Thanks as always.

460
00:37:47,182 --> 00:37:48,850
- Goodness.
-  Damn it.

461
00:37:49,559 --> 00:37:51,394
Have a safe trip back, okay?

462
00:37:57,400 --> 00:38:00,403
I told you to just suck it up,
and you couldn't even do that?

463
00:38:01,112 --> 00:38:03,030
I don't know who he's connected to,

464
00:38:03,031 --> 00:38:05,991
but he forced his way into becoming
the head of the fisheries co-op.

465
00:38:05,992 --> 00:38:08,285
He's got the village's finances
on a tight leash

466
00:38:08,286 --> 00:38:10,496
so all of Pyeondongdo
is basically at his mercy!

467
00:38:10,497 --> 00:38:14,208
Rub him the wrong way,
and we could really end up in big trouble!

468
00:38:14,209 --> 00:38:15,501
You're killing me!

469
00:38:15,502 --> 00:38:16,503
So…

470
00:38:17,921 --> 00:38:19,588
are you saying I was in the wrong?

471
00:38:19,589 --> 00:38:23,009
You doctors won't have to deal with this
once you leave after a year.

472
00:38:23,760 --> 00:38:24,927
What?

473
00:38:24,928 --> 00:38:28,639
Once you leave, that'll be it for you.
But those of us left behind will suffer.

474
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:32,227
But Dr. Chiyeon also did what he did
for our center.

475
00:38:33,895 --> 00:38:37,357
- No, what I meant to say is…
-  I understand your concerns.

476
00:38:38,107 --> 00:38:39,442
I was out of line.

477
00:38:40,860 --> 00:38:42,946
Dr. Hyeon…

478
00:38:50,453 --> 00:38:54,374
Come on, Doctor.
What I meant to say was…

479
00:38:56,251 --> 00:38:58,794
Why's he getting so worked up about that?

480
00:38:58,795 --> 00:39:01,296
It's not like you lied about them leaving.

481
00:39:01,297 --> 00:39:05,718
The PH docs were the first to always
draw a line between us, weren't they?

482
00:39:10,765 --> 00:39:12,891
I mean, think back to Dr. Do's interview.

483
00:39:12,892 --> 00:39:15,936
Ms. Hari was the one who saved him,

484
00:39:15,937 --> 00:39:18,939
but he didn't even say
a single word about her.

485
00:39:18,940 --> 00:39:20,984
- I'm okay with--
- Hey!

486
00:39:33,955 --> 00:39:37,584
I usually eat three slices.

487
00:39:38,084 --> 00:39:39,961
May I take the two remaining slices?

488
00:39:40,753 --> 00:39:43,006
- Sure.
- Then I'll get going now.

489
00:39:47,719 --> 00:39:48,720
Careful.

490
00:39:50,930 --> 00:39:53,098
- Take care.
- My throat is parched.

491
00:39:53,099 --> 00:39:55,226
- Can I also take a soda?
-  Sure.

492
00:39:56,853 --> 00:39:57,936
See you.

493
00:40:01,649 --> 00:40:03,609
Ms. Yuk Hari.

494
00:40:03,610 --> 00:40:06,988
I suggest you pick a side and stick to it.

495
00:40:08,156 --> 00:40:09,157
Okay.

496
00:40:10,617 --> 00:40:12,534
Whoa, Dr. Yong.

497
00:40:12,535 --> 00:40:15,913
From now on, I'm just going to do my job
and nothing else,

498
00:40:15,914 --> 00:40:17,582
since I'll be leaving anyway!

499
00:40:22,128 --> 00:40:24,255
I'm on your side, by the way.

500
00:40:24,881 --> 00:40:26,049
How about you, Dr. Do?

501
00:40:27,634 --> 00:40:29,134
What?

502
00:40:29,135 --> 00:40:32,012
I'm asking whose side you're on, okay?

503
00:40:32,013 --> 00:40:36,350
Are you with the PH docs having ramyeon,
or the nurses having pizza?

504
00:40:36,351 --> 00:40:37,602
Pick a side.

505
00:40:41,981 --> 00:40:44,483
I'm on your side.

506
00:40:44,484 --> 00:40:46,152
- Right?
- Yeah.

507
00:40:47,904 --> 00:40:50,031
This is so frustrating.

508
00:40:58,247 --> 00:41:00,667
The PH docs feel like
we really let them down, right?

509
00:41:02,627 --> 00:41:03,670
Yes. Kind of.

510
00:41:07,423 --> 00:41:09,342
The nurses must
also be really angry. Right?

511
00:41:10,343 --> 00:41:12,428
- Yes. Kind of.
- Oh…

512
00:41:14,013 --> 00:41:16,223
If people found out
we were dating in secret,

513
00:41:16,224 --> 00:41:18,518
- the fallout would be catastrophic.
- Very.

514
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:24,523
I'm going outside,
so count to 100 before you come.

515
00:41:24,524 --> 00:41:25,607
One hundred?

516
00:41:25,608 --> 00:41:31,613
LUCKY SUPERMARKET

517
00:41:31,614 --> 00:41:36,994
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten…

518
00:41:36,995 --> 00:41:39,663
It's like you two don't even see me!

519
00:41:39,664 --> 00:41:41,790
…three, four, five,
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

520
00:41:41,791 --> 00:41:42,792
One hundred!

521
00:41:46,796 --> 00:41:49,382
- Go.
- Hurry up and go.

522
00:41:55,054 --> 00:41:58,223
I'm okay. You should go.

523
00:42:03,896 --> 00:42:07,315
It's time to order
next year's medicinal ingredients.

524
00:42:07,316 --> 00:42:11,945
If you doctors need anything,
we need to submit a form for it.

525
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:16,492
So please go over your patient charts
carefully and turn them in.

526
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:18,910
Please submit these by this week.

527
00:42:18,911 --> 00:42:19,996
Sure.

528
00:42:28,671 --> 00:42:33,092
But how are we supposed to know which
ingredients we'll be needing next year

529
00:42:34,594 --> 00:42:36,053
when we'll be leaving soon?

530
00:42:36,054 --> 00:42:37,387
Well…

531
00:42:41,100 --> 00:42:43,770
It's what every doctor
before you did before leaving.

532
00:42:45,354 --> 00:42:47,857
I guess I didn't know
since I'm leaving soon anyway.

533
00:42:49,525 --> 00:42:51,110
Well, now that you know, do it.

534
00:42:51,819 --> 00:42:54,613
No! I can't do it!

535
00:42:54,614 --> 00:42:56,782
What the…

536
00:42:56,783 --> 00:43:00,619
Why are you guys fighting? Huh?

537
00:43:00,620 --> 00:43:01,996
Gosh!

538
00:43:07,126 --> 00:43:08,960
I'm sorry for yelling.

539
00:43:08,961 --> 00:43:12,965
I'm also sorry. I didn't mean it, either.

540
00:43:13,758 --> 00:43:14,759
We received a fax.

541
00:43:18,137 --> 00:43:19,138
Huh?

542
00:43:20,890 --> 00:43:21,974
What is it?

543
00:43:24,185 --> 00:43:25,186
Dr. Do.

544
00:43:26,104 --> 00:43:28,940
It says you're to report
to Yeopoong-gun starting tomorrow.

545
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:36,196
NOTICE OF REASSIGNMENT

546
00:43:36,197 --> 00:43:38,116
"Notice of reassignment"?

547
00:43:40,284 --> 00:43:43,579
"…required to report
to the Yeopoong-gun public health center"?

548
00:43:50,962 --> 00:43:53,547
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER DIRECTOR
CHOI HYANGMI

549
00:43:58,553 --> 00:43:59,554
Hello?

550
00:44:00,263 --> 00:44:03,056
Ms. Choi, this is Dr. Do Jiui,
the PH doc from Pyeondongdo.

551
00:44:03,057 --> 00:44:05,434
I just received a notice of reassignment.

552
00:44:06,269 --> 00:44:09,938
I guess the governor
really took a liking to you, Dr. Do,

553
00:44:09,939 --> 00:44:12,608
judging by how quickly he summoned you.

554
00:44:13,776 --> 00:44:18,196
It's just that I'm having a hard time
accepting such a sudden reassignment.

555
00:44:18,197 --> 00:44:19,240
Dr. Do Jiui,

556
00:44:19,782 --> 00:44:23,286
any qualms you have about the matter
are irrelevant.

557
00:44:24,954 --> 00:44:27,540
You are a civil servant and a soldier.

558
00:44:28,332 --> 00:44:31,544
If you don't follow orders,
you will face severe penalties.

559
00:44:32,795 --> 00:44:36,340
I get that you're
emotionally invested in the island.

560
00:44:37,049 --> 00:44:40,761
But you're not from there anyway.

561
00:44:42,054 --> 00:44:46,142
Just think of this as an early farewell.

562
00:44:47,435 --> 00:44:49,353
I'll see you tomorrow at Yeopoong-gun.

563
00:45:01,782 --> 00:45:03,743
Dr. Do, are you busy today?

564
00:45:05,494 --> 00:45:08,164
I know that you're disappointed in me.

565
00:45:09,498 --> 00:45:13,085
But since this'll be your last day here,
we should have a meal together.

566
00:45:16,172 --> 00:45:19,883
I know that I'm a coward.

567
00:45:19,884 --> 00:45:23,387
Hey, why would you say that?

568
00:45:24,430 --> 00:45:26,389
But what other choice did I have? Huh?

569
00:45:26,390 --> 00:45:31,437
Any trouble we stir up with that sorry lot
would only end up harming our patients.

570
00:45:32,271 --> 00:45:33,813
That's why I did what I did.

571
00:45:33,814 --> 00:45:38,068
I wasn't scolding you
because you would be leaving soon.

572
00:45:38,069 --> 00:45:41,363
Absolutely not!

573
00:45:41,364 --> 00:45:46,160
So if you hold any grudges against me,
let them go before you leave.

574
00:45:47,536 --> 00:45:48,537
Here…

575
00:45:52,583 --> 00:45:55,669
I prepared this as soon as
I got the call from you, Ms. Sinhye.

576
00:45:55,670 --> 00:45:56,921
Right.

577
00:45:57,672 --> 00:46:01,049
You asked me to prepare it
with the freshest catch.

578
00:46:01,050 --> 00:46:03,468
So I went there myself
to get my hands on these.

579
00:46:03,469 --> 00:46:04,552
Well done.

580
00:46:04,553 --> 00:46:07,847
I wanted to serve up my best dish.

581
00:46:07,848 --> 00:46:09,267
Thank you.

582
00:46:10,351 --> 00:46:12,770
You'd never find a dish like this
on the mainland.

583
00:46:13,562 --> 00:46:15,648
It's going to blow your mind
once you try it.

584
00:46:41,299 --> 00:46:42,966
It's delicious.

585
00:46:42,967 --> 00:46:44,218
What a relief.

586
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:46,971
Eat your fill, Dr. Do.

587
00:46:47,596 --> 00:46:50,141
Eat up.

588
00:46:51,475 --> 00:46:52,767
Yes, eat.

589
00:46:52,768 --> 00:46:55,020
You're drunk. Stop drinking.

590
00:47:02,987 --> 00:47:04,946
Pull yourself together.

591
00:47:04,947 --> 00:47:06,656
Why did you drink so much?

592
00:47:06,657 --> 00:47:10,452
Why do you care if I drink or not?

593
00:47:10,453 --> 00:47:15,206
I drank because I'm frustrated. So what?

594
00:47:15,207 --> 00:47:17,710
Are you that frustrated
that Dr. Jiui's leaving?

595
00:47:19,086 --> 00:47:21,463
Everyone leaves.

596
00:47:21,464 --> 00:47:23,215
They all do eventually.

597
00:47:24,258 --> 00:47:25,801
Let go of me.

598
00:47:35,227 --> 00:47:36,312
Hey.

599
00:47:37,730 --> 00:47:40,066
I'd like to ask you something.

600
00:47:43,277 --> 00:47:45,321
Why do you keep wearing
such uncomfortable shoes?

601
00:47:47,156 --> 00:47:48,657
Why do you care?

602
00:47:49,325 --> 00:47:50,701
It bothers me.

603
00:47:54,330 --> 00:47:56,916
Then just take them back.

604
00:47:57,416 --> 00:47:59,835
Pretend it never happened.

605
00:48:01,128 --> 00:48:06,174
Taking back a gift doesn't change
the fact that I gave it to you.

606
00:48:06,175 --> 00:48:09,594
We both know
exactly what happened that day!

607
00:48:09,595 --> 00:48:12,014
Stop running your mouth.

608
00:48:13,099 --> 00:48:15,643
You talk way too much.

609
00:48:16,894 --> 00:48:18,145
I'm going to say it.

610
00:48:19,021 --> 00:48:20,773
What happened that day…

611
00:48:22,775 --> 00:48:23,943
I liked it.

612
00:48:24,944 --> 00:48:28,072
I also liked
the things we talked about, and…

613
00:48:31,409 --> 00:48:33,160
My point is I definitely liked it.

614
00:48:33,744 --> 00:48:35,204
What use is any of that?

615
00:48:35,788 --> 00:48:38,039
You'll be leaving eventually.

616
00:48:38,040 --> 00:48:40,708
Isn't that why you don't bother
to sew up your clothes?

617
00:48:40,709 --> 00:48:43,379
Because you'll be leaving soon anyway?

618
00:48:45,673 --> 00:48:48,634
Is that what's been bothering you?

619
00:48:50,386 --> 00:48:54,514
I mean, if you care so much
about the holes in my shirt,

620
00:48:54,515 --> 00:48:56,642
why won't you wear the slippers I got you?

621
00:48:58,102 --> 00:48:59,936
Because they're wasted on me!

622
00:48:59,937 --> 00:49:03,356
A country bumpkin like me
doesn't have the guts to strut around

623
00:49:03,357 --> 00:49:05,776
wearing something so valuable on my feet!

624
00:49:40,269 --> 00:49:42,897
Did you have a lot to drink?

625
00:49:44,523 --> 00:49:45,858
Yes.

626
00:49:47,234 --> 00:49:49,028
Because I'm happy.

627
00:49:50,821 --> 00:49:53,656
We couldn't have asked
for a better outcome.

628
00:49:53,657 --> 00:49:58,119
You won't have to cross
the ocean you fear so much anymore.

629
00:49:58,120 --> 00:50:01,748
And we'll be free to go on all the dates
we want on the mainland,

630
00:50:01,749 --> 00:50:05,127
unlike our current arrangement here.

631
00:50:07,087 --> 00:50:08,422
Man, this is great.

632
00:50:10,049 --> 00:50:12,760
- Are you really okay with it?
- Huh?

633
00:50:22,478 --> 00:50:23,521
No.

634
00:50:25,814 --> 00:50:28,399
Dr. Do,

635
00:50:28,400 --> 00:50:31,320
please don't leave me.

636
00:50:32,154 --> 00:50:34,614
Stay by my side.

637
00:50:34,615 --> 00:50:37,868
I wish you would stay by my side.

638
00:50:39,912 --> 00:50:42,331
You're really drunk.

639
00:50:43,624 --> 00:50:45,209
Stay by my side.

640
00:51:03,978 --> 00:51:05,895
You all said you wouldn't come see me off.

641
00:51:05,896 --> 00:51:08,606
Well, the port just happens to be
on my route to work,

642
00:51:08,607 --> 00:51:11,359
so I'm just standing here
to take a quick breather.

643
00:51:11,360 --> 00:51:12,527
Don't mind me.

644
00:51:12,528 --> 00:51:15,239
- I was also just passing by.
-  Mm-hmm.

645
00:51:15,948 --> 00:51:18,701
Why are you acting like
you didn't come out here on purpose?

646
00:51:19,285 --> 00:51:20,578
You're so weird.

647
00:51:32,715 --> 00:51:34,258
Dr. Do!

648
00:51:35,968 --> 00:51:37,136
Deokhwa!

649
00:51:38,429 --> 00:51:39,430
Careful!

650
00:51:45,561 --> 00:51:48,688
We got back to the island
after she was discharged yesterday,

651
00:51:48,689 --> 00:51:50,773
but we didn't get a chance to stop by.

652
00:51:50,774 --> 00:51:52,610
Here's a gift for you, Dr. Do.

653
00:51:54,361 --> 00:51:55,404
It's for me?

654
00:51:55,904 --> 00:52:00,158
I'm also going to become a superhero
who saves people's lives, just like you.

655
00:52:04,538 --> 00:52:06,372
Thank you, Deokhwa.

656
00:52:06,373 --> 00:52:08,834
- You'll come visit, right?
- I will.

657
00:52:18,177 --> 00:52:19,178
I'll get going now.

658
00:52:21,138 --> 00:52:22,306
I'll get going.

659
00:52:28,437 --> 00:52:32,524
The ferry bound for Yeopoong
will be departing soon.

660
00:52:33,525 --> 00:52:37,404
To all remaining passengers,
please board the ferry right away.

661
00:52:41,742 --> 00:52:43,911
Let's go back now, okay?

662
00:54:01,488 --> 00:54:04,073
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER
DO JIUI

663
00:54:04,074 --> 00:54:05,743
Can you turn to the right for us?

664
00:54:06,744 --> 00:54:07,953
Smile, please.

665
00:54:08,620 --> 00:54:10,664
Make a bigger heart. Bigger!

666
00:54:11,331 --> 00:54:13,375
- Okay.
- Give us a cheek heart too.

667
00:54:14,209 --> 00:54:15,376
A cheek heart.

668
00:54:15,377 --> 00:54:19,088
-  Thank you.
- A cheek heart. While smiling.

669
00:54:19,089 --> 00:54:23,718
The other side too.
Both sides. That's great.

670
00:54:23,719 --> 00:54:24,802
That's great.

671
00:54:24,803 --> 00:54:26,472
Okay, that's enough for today.

672
00:54:27,097 --> 00:54:29,432
- Thank you, everyone.
- Thank you.

673
00:54:29,433 --> 00:54:32,644
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

674
00:54:33,187 --> 00:54:34,897
Dr. Do, go grab a meal then come back.

675
00:54:35,647 --> 00:54:38,609
We'll be having a PR shoot
for the modernization initiative.

676
00:54:40,277 --> 00:54:41,278
But…

677
00:54:42,571 --> 00:54:45,824
wasn't I transferred to Yeopoong-gun
to serve as a PH doc?

678
00:54:48,076 --> 00:54:50,996
How am I going to treat patients
if I'm busy taking photos?

679
00:54:51,705 --> 00:54:54,666
I haven't even had the time
to go over the patients' charts yet.

680
00:54:55,542 --> 00:54:57,544
You don't have to treat any patients.

681
00:54:58,629 --> 00:55:00,463
What else would a doctor do?

682
00:55:00,464 --> 00:55:03,383
You're due to join the governor tomorrow
for his interview.

683
00:55:04,092 --> 00:55:06,470
You've had your hair done, right?

684
00:55:07,346 --> 00:55:10,182
Hmm. Here's your schedule for tomorrow.

685
00:55:15,896 --> 00:55:17,772
DR. DO JIUI'S SCHEDULE
FOR OCTOBER 1

686
00:55:17,773 --> 00:55:19,608
- Let's go, Ms. Choi.
-  Okay.

687
00:55:47,052 --> 00:55:49,304
Man, that tastes like crap.

688
00:55:59,189 --> 00:56:00,856
Do Jiui!

689
00:56:00,857 --> 00:56:03,484
Do Jiui!

690
00:56:03,485 --> 00:56:05,903
Having fun on the mainland?

691
00:56:05,904 --> 00:56:08,239
Having fun on the mainland?

692
00:56:08,240 --> 00:56:14,871
We haven't even been apart
for that long, but I miss you already!

693
00:56:15,539 --> 00:56:17,207
I said, I miss you!

694
00:56:17,916 --> 00:56:19,835
I said, I miss you!

695
00:57:05,088 --> 00:57:06,298
You're here early.

696
00:57:09,760 --> 00:57:10,761
Ms. Yuk.

697
00:57:12,095 --> 00:57:13,972
Can we talk for a moment?

698
00:57:15,307 --> 00:57:17,225
Why? Did something happen?

699
00:57:25,942 --> 00:57:26,943
Dr. Do Jiui.

700
00:57:27,944 --> 00:57:30,863
Here's your schedule
for this week's press tour.

701
00:57:30,864 --> 00:57:33,200
Let me know if you need anything.

702
00:57:44,002 --> 00:57:47,130
It's one interview after another.
Man, this is so…

703
00:58:13,699 --> 00:58:14,700
Are you busy?

704
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:18,829
Give me a call, Ms. Yuk.

705
00:58:34,970 --> 00:58:37,054
YEOPOONG ILBO
YEOPOONG'S PERSON OF THE MONTH

706
00:58:37,055 --> 00:58:39,641
HEALTHCARE MODERNIZATION
IN UNDERSERVED ISLANDS

707
00:58:40,434 --> 00:58:42,935
Why'd they put this in my room?

708
00:58:42,936 --> 00:58:44,312
I'm so sick of it all.

709
00:58:56,533 --> 00:58:59,202
MS. YUK HARI

710
00:59:01,329 --> 00:59:03,915
Ms. Yuk, is something wrong?

711
00:59:08,003 --> 00:59:09,212
I'm worried about you.

712
00:59:34,321 --> 00:59:36,531
"I'd like to impart a proposal to you."

713
00:59:38,492 --> 00:59:39,576
"Impart"?

714
00:59:43,538 --> 00:59:46,666
"I'd like to make a proposal."

715
00:59:53,215 --> 00:59:56,133
With the esteemed Dr. Do Jiui by my side,

716
00:59:56,134 --> 01:00:01,305
I'd just really like to try,

717
01:00:01,306 --> 01:00:04,225
to try as hard as hell,

718
01:00:04,226 --> 01:00:08,395
to bring the modernization of healthcare
in Yeopoong-gun into reality.

719
01:00:08,396 --> 01:00:10,397
Thank you
for sharing your dedication

720
01:00:10,398 --> 01:00:12,650
to achieving healthcare modernization.

721
01:00:12,651 --> 01:00:15,611
But judging by the look
on the doctor's face,

722
01:00:15,612 --> 01:00:17,613
it seems he's got something to say.

723
01:00:17,614 --> 01:00:20,116
Would you mind sharing it with us?

724
01:00:26,498 --> 01:00:29,501
I'd like to make a proposal.

725
01:00:31,044 --> 01:00:32,127
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

726
01:00:32,128 --> 01:00:34,088
What? At the port?

727
01:00:34,089 --> 01:00:35,257
Yes, I understand.

728
01:00:37,050 --> 01:00:39,302
- It's a fall injury patient. Get ready.
- Okay.

729
01:00:39,970 --> 01:00:41,096
Dr. Chiyeon!

730
01:00:41,721 --> 01:00:42,722
Dr. Chiyeon!

731
01:00:43,348 --> 01:00:45,349
We have a fall injury patient at the port!

732
01:00:45,350 --> 01:00:47,269
- A fall injury?
- Yes. Hurry.

733
01:00:53,400 --> 01:00:54,483
DANGER
DO NOT APPROACH

734
01:00:54,484 --> 01:00:56,735
Excuse us, move aside please.

735
01:00:56,736 --> 01:00:58,572
I'm sorry. Please move aside.

736
01:01:04,578 --> 01:01:05,661
Let's flush the wound.

737
01:01:05,662 --> 01:01:07,371
- Some saline please.
- Okay.

738
01:01:07,372 --> 01:01:08,956
We need a splint to hold his ankle.

739
01:01:08,957 --> 01:01:10,124
Okay.

740
01:01:13,753 --> 01:01:15,129
It's an open fracture.

741
01:01:15,130 --> 01:01:17,464
We'll need some clean cloth
for an elastic bandage.

742
01:01:17,465 --> 01:01:19,383
BONE EXPOSED THROUGH SKIN

743
01:01:19,384 --> 01:01:20,385
ELASTIC BANDAGE

744
01:01:22,053 --> 01:01:24,180
Please hold him down.
Setting the bone now.

745
01:01:33,356 --> 01:01:34,566
It's been realigned.

746
01:01:42,824 --> 01:01:44,200
- More saline please.
- Okay.

747
01:02:15,607 --> 01:02:19,360
Every half hour, keep tightening and
loosening the tourniquet for five minutes.

748
01:02:19,361 --> 01:02:21,320
Yes, I understand.
We'll take it from here.

749
01:02:21,321 --> 01:02:23,030
- Okay.
- Thank you for your hard work.

750
01:02:23,031 --> 01:02:25,115
- Thank you.
- Are you doing okay?

751
01:02:25,116 --> 01:02:26,200
Yes.

752
01:02:29,412 --> 01:02:31,873
Oh, my. Good work, everyone.

753
01:02:32,999 --> 01:02:35,085
- Well done, Dr. Jiui.
- Thanks.

754
01:02:36,086 --> 01:02:37,087
Goodness.

755
01:02:40,423 --> 01:02:41,424
Huh?

756
01:02:42,300 --> 01:02:43,301
Huh?

757
01:02:45,679 --> 01:02:48,348
Wait, Dr. Jiui. What are you doing here?

758
01:02:48,932 --> 01:02:50,934
My transfer's been canceled.

759
01:02:52,227 --> 01:02:53,269
What?

760
01:02:54,145 --> 01:02:55,563
I see.

761
01:02:56,606 --> 01:02:57,857
So that's how it is.

762
01:03:09,411 --> 01:03:10,536
ON-SITE ISSUES

763
01:03:10,537 --> 01:03:12,037
BRINGING YOU THE NEWS
LIVE ON THE SCENE

764
01:03:12,038 --> 01:03:13,915
Like you said, Governor,

765
01:03:14,457 --> 01:03:16,208
I don't want island residents to think

766
01:03:16,209 --> 01:03:19,378
that death is the only option
when they get sick.

767
01:03:19,379 --> 01:03:21,296
Of course!

768
01:03:21,297 --> 01:03:22,298
So please,

769
01:03:23,133 --> 01:03:26,761
send me back to Pyeondongdo.

770
01:03:27,846 --> 01:03:29,972
As a doctor,
I shouldn't be in front of a camera…

771
01:03:29,973 --> 01:03:31,640
"WHAT'S HE SAYING?"

772
01:03:31,641 --> 01:03:33,226
…but in front of patients.

773
01:03:33,810 --> 01:03:37,104
Mr. Do Jiui's remark reminds us
of the true purpose

774
01:03:37,105 --> 01:03:38,647
of the public health system

775
01:03:38,648 --> 01:03:41,859
which sends doctors to underserved regions
in place of military service.

776
01:03:41,860 --> 01:03:44,237
That concludes
our weekly on-site issue segment.

777
01:03:45,989 --> 01:03:47,656
Well, I'll be.

778
01:03:47,657 --> 01:03:51,660
To think he'd dare to screw me over
like that in front of the reporters.

779
01:03:51,661 --> 01:03:52,745
I'm sorry, sir.

780
01:03:52,746 --> 01:03:54,496
I won't let him get away with this.

781
01:03:54,497 --> 01:03:56,249
Just wait and see how I deal with him!

782
01:03:56,833 --> 01:03:58,417
That…

783
01:03:58,418 --> 01:03:59,877
You're dead.

784
01:03:59,878 --> 01:04:01,421
I won't let you get away with this!

785
01:04:02,505 --> 01:04:04,548
Damn it.

786
01:04:04,549 --> 01:04:05,633
And that…

787
01:04:06,259 --> 01:04:07,552
is why I'm back for good.

788
01:04:08,178 --> 01:04:09,637
I won't be leaving anytime soon.

789
01:04:10,472 --> 01:04:12,556
So he told you to tell him what you want,

790
01:04:12,557 --> 01:04:15,559
- and you asked him to send you back here?
- Yeah.

791
01:04:15,560 --> 01:04:17,937
Why'd you answer Pyeondongdo,
of all places?

792
01:04:18,438 --> 01:04:20,189
You should have said Gyeonggi-do.

793
01:04:22,692 --> 01:04:25,320
You really crack me up, Dr. Yong.

794
01:04:25,945 --> 01:04:27,863
You didn't even get the joke.

795
01:04:27,864 --> 01:04:29,615
He should have asked
to be sent to a different island?

796
01:04:29,616 --> 01:04:32,159
Gyeonggi-do's not actually an island.

797
01:04:41,669 --> 01:04:43,004
Is something wrong?

798
01:04:46,674 --> 01:04:48,885
Are you shocked
because I suddenly came back?

799
01:04:53,223 --> 01:04:55,016
Why was it so hard to reach you?

800
01:04:56,476 --> 01:05:00,814
I know you were busy,
but you could have at least checked in.

801
01:05:03,942 --> 01:05:05,568
I was really worried about you.

802
01:05:07,112 --> 01:05:09,322
I thought something might have happened.

803
01:05:15,120 --> 01:05:16,454
Are you mad at me?

804
01:05:18,331 --> 01:05:19,582
Why didn't you tell me…

805
01:05:21,960 --> 01:05:23,253
that my grandma

806
01:05:24,712 --> 01:05:26,339
gave up on life?

807
01:05:28,675 --> 01:05:30,551
Ms. Yuk, well…

808
01:05:30,552 --> 01:05:31,719
I'm going to…

809
01:05:33,054 --> 01:05:35,430
I'm going to convince her
to change her mind.

810
01:05:35,431 --> 01:05:37,267
I'd be nothing without my grandma.

811
01:05:40,854 --> 01:05:42,522
So, Dr. Do…

812
01:05:47,277 --> 01:05:48,862
help me change her mind.

813
01:05:58,496 --> 01:05:59,539
You can't do it?

814
01:06:04,169 --> 01:06:07,297
Because you're a doctor
who has to respect his patients' wishes?

815
01:06:16,931 --> 01:06:18,933
Can't you do it for me, not as a doctor…

816
01:06:22,770 --> 01:06:24,522
but as my boyfriend?

817
01:06:34,324 --> 01:06:35,533
I'm sorry.

818
01:07:18,993 --> 01:07:22,329
CAN'T YOU DO IT FOR ME,
NOT AS A DOCTOR…

819
01:07:22,330 --> 01:07:29,295
BUT AS MY BOYFRIEND?

820
01:07:37,679 --> 01:07:41,099
THIS IS THE MOMENT
THEIR ROMANCE TRULY TAKES OFF

821
01:07:45,687 --> 01:07:49,107
RUNNING LINES
UNTIL THE VERY LAST MOMENT

822
01:07:57,198 --> 01:08:00,200
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

823
01:08:00,201 --> 01:08:02,661
It would have been better
if you hadn't returned.

824
01:08:02,662 --> 01:08:04,871
I have nothing to say to you,
Dr. Do.

825
01:08:04,872 --> 01:08:09,335
Can you stay by Hari's side
for just a little while longer?

826
01:08:09,919 --> 01:08:12,046
I would have chosen otherwise.

827
01:08:13,506 --> 01:08:14,881
Are you getting ready to die?

828
01:08:14,882 --> 01:08:17,092
Why are you sorting things out?

829
01:08:17,093 --> 01:08:18,510
Oh, no!

830
01:08:18,511 --> 01:08:20,304
Yes.

831
01:08:20,305 --> 01:08:22,140
We need a medical chopper!

832
01:08:22,849 --> 01:08:25,684
-  Patient shows no signs of life.
-  You can't leave us like this!

833
01:08:30,023 --> 01:08:32,025
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park
